Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> program
Rule 1     program -> statement_list
Rule 2     statement_list -> statement_list statement
Rule 3     statement_list -> statement
Rule 4     statement -> LET IDENTIFIER ASSIGN expression
Rule 5     statement -> IDENTIFIER ASSIGN expression
Rule 6     statement -> PRINT LPAREN expression RPAREN
Rule 7     statement -> IF expression LBRACE statement_list RBRACE
Rule 8     statement -> IF expression LBRACE statement_list RBRACE ELSE LBRACE statement_list RBRACE
Rule 9     statement -> WHILE expression LBRACE statement_list RBRACE
Rule 10    expression -> expression EQ expression
Rule 11    expression -> expression NE expression
Rule 12    expression -> expression LT expression
Rule 13    expression -> expression LE expression
Rule 14    expression -> expression GT expression
Rule 15    expression -> expression GE expression
Rule 16    expression -> expression PLUS expression
Rule 17    expression -> expression MINUS expression
Rule 18    expression -> expression MULTIPLY expression
Rule 19    expression -> expression DIVIDE expression
Rule 20    expression -> INTEGER
Rule 21    expression -> IDENTIFIER
Rule 22    expression -> LPAREN expression RPAREN

Terminals, with rules where they appear

ASSIGN               : 4 5
DIVIDE               : 19
ELSE                 : 8
EQ                   : 10
GE                   : 15
GT                   : 14
IDENTIFIER           : 4 5 21
IF                   : 7 8
INTEGER              : 20
LBRACE               : 7 8 8 9
LE                   : 13
LET                  : 4
LPAREN               : 6 22
LT                   : 12
MINUS                : 17
MULTIPLY             : 18
NE                   : 11
PLUS                 : 16
PRINT                : 6
RBRACE               : 7 8 8 9
RPAREN               : 6 22
WHILE                : 9
error                : 

